## âš™ï¸ Local Setup

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ts2004T/codeclutch-backend.git
cd codeclutch-backend

2ï¸âƒ£ Backend Setup
cd backend
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate    # Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt


Create .env:

OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_api_key_here


Run backend:

uvicorn main:app --reload


Backend runs at:

http://localhost:8000

3ï¸âƒ£ Frontend Setup
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev


Frontend runs at:

http://localhost:5173

ğŸ”Œ API Overview
POST /analyze-resume
{
  "resume_text": "Python, React, FastAPI"
}

POST /generate-questions
{
  "skills": ["Python", "React"]
}

POST /evaluate-answers
{
  "qa_pairs": [
    {
      "question": "Explain Python decorators",
      "answer": "Decorators allow..."
    }
  ]
}

ğŸ¯ Design Goals

Interview-focused (not overengineered)
Clean, readable, interview-quality code
Strong type safety via Pydantic
No database (stateless API)
Clear separation of concerns

ğŸ” Environment Variables
Variable	Description
OPENROUTER_API_KEY	API key for OpenRouter

ğŸ“Œ Notes

No authentication (by design)
LLM responses validated via model_validate_json
Designed for college placements & internships

